body:
So its fair for Riot to put you into a lower priority queue if you have afk'd during a match, I'm chill with that. The fact that bothers me is when you're waiting for say 20 minutes, you have to stay in the lobby on the screen saying, "Low Priority Queue". You have to stay on this screen until you wait your time up and get into champ select, or you just leave the queue, however, leaving the queue results in you having to wait again if you want to play another game. 

Personally, I find this very stupid, I can not interact at all with friends online or change my runes or go into my collection or even look in the store. I think this feature should be changed. Keep the low priority/ leaver buster thing of course, but make it so I can at least interact with the client instead of waiting there for 20 minutes just to talk to one of my friends.
 {{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}
